<br>
When pets were KoS to mobs in the old days, it used to cause LOTS of problems, particularly in dungeons, when a pet would get lost/wander off trying to follow it's owner.  It would run into mobs while lost and get killed.  Then the mobs would all come to kill the pets owner and his/her friends. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 11:23:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Research for Dracca</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The only real advantage to water was that it would regen hp faster than the others,<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Water pets also have very, very high poison resistance; at least at low levels this makes them extremely useful for fighting snakes and other poisonous mobs that many players avoid because they don't want to take the extra poison damage. I flew through some of the lower levels that way, since those mobs often did less pure combat damage than others of their level.<br>
<br>
Personally, when I've actually had a water pet available it's been my pet of choice when I didn't need any of the special abilities of the other pets, since it does a decent job in any circumstances. I'd certainly use the others when I needed a good DS, root or caster stunning, but for fighting a mixture of mobs water seems the best. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 2:40:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=37>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Research for Dracca</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I just really don't lke the air one because the little guy keeps disappearing on me. He SAYS that he is guarding me but he is always disapearing. BAH!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
